name: Lead
technicalDescription: Sawtooth oscillator, bright cutting tone, 0.5s sustain
yourListeningNotes: synth, soft not bright, very round

name: Impact
technicalDescription: Thick James Blake pad, fatsawtooth (3 detuned), warm wide character, slow attack
yourListeningNotes: Synth, very sawtooth, serrated knife sound, not warm

name: Sweep
technicalDescription: Radiohead/Prophet-5 style, triangle wave, round smooth analog, gentle filter sweep
yourListeningNotes: Synth, round and warm like a  big plastic tube, with a bit of bite

name: Vocal Chop
technicalDescription: Ethereal theremin-like, haunting ghostly, sine wave, slow attack (300ms), long release (2s)
yourListeningNotes: Synth, really wide, like a bell, very round

name: Sub
technicalDescription: Deep sub bass, pure sine with minimal harmonics, dark low-frequency focused

name: Wobble
technicalDescription: FM synthesis, 0.5 harmonicity, modulated bass character

name: Pad
technicalDescription: Grand piano Salamander samples, realistic acoustic piano

name: Pluck
technicalDescription: Sine wave bass, rich sustained, warm full-bodied with subtle harmonics
yourListeningNotes: Sine wav bass that sounds like a super clean sine tone at higher registers

name: Arp
technicalDescription: Square wave, short staccato envelope (attack 5ms, release 300ms), one-shot

name: Kick
technicalDescription: Bass drum, pitch decay, 10 octaves sweep

name: Noise
yourListeningNotes: Noise, can act as a snare for electro and video game songs

name: Snare
technicalDescription: White noise, snare character, 200ms decay, one-shot
yourListeningNotes: Noise slap, can and as snare

name: Clap
technicalDescription: Pink noise, hand clap character, 150ms decay, one-shot
yourListeningNotes: Noise slap, almost like a high pitched punch

name: Glitch
technicalDescription: Metallic percussion, 100Hz, high modulation, very short (50ms), one-shot
yourListeningNotes: Closed  hi hat, very short, like a tick,
